# 07 - Adapters

## Purpose

This document defines the role of adapters within the Nyx architecture.

Adapters connect external development environments to the Nyx engine without introducing platform-specific protection behavior.

---

# What Is an Adapter?

An adapter is an integration layer between Nyx and an external development environment.

Examples include:

* Visual Studio Code
* JetBrains IDEs
* Visual Studio
* Godot Editor
* Unreal Editor
* Automation platforms

Adapters improve developer workflow while keeping protection behavior consistent.

---

# Responsibilities

Adapters are responsible for:

* Invoking the CLI or Engine API
* Presenting user-friendly interfaces
* Managing editor-specific interactions
* Displaying execution results
* Integrating with platform workflows

Adapters should remain lightweight.

---

# Non-Responsibilities

Adapters must not:

* implement protection algorithms
* implement protection capabilities
* modify protection behavior
* interpret protection policies
* produce platform-specific protection results

Protection behavior always belongs to the engine.

---

# Design Goals

Every adapter should:

* feel native to its platform
* remain lightweight
* be easy to maintain
* minimize duplicated logic
* remain compatible with future engine versions

Adapters are expected to evolve independently from the protection engine.

---

# Supported Integration Styles

Depending on the platform, adapters may expose Nyx through:

* Commands
* Menus
* Context menus
* Tool windows
* Editor actions
* Build hooks
* Automation tasks

The interaction model may vary.

Protection behavior must not.

---

# Platform Independence

The protection engine should never require changes because a new adapter is introduced.

Adding support for a new editor or platform should involve implementing a new adapter rather than modifying the engine.

---

# Future Adapters

The architecture intentionally allows additional integrations without changing the existing design.

Examples include:

* Neovim
* Emacs
* Eclipse
* Rider
* Fleet
* Custom enterprise tooling

The list is intentionally open-ended.

---

# Summary

Adapters are integration components.

They improve accessibility and developer experience while preserving a single, consistent protection engine across every supported platform.
